(FAQ 1: WHAT GPA DO I NEED?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(There is no single GPA rule for every scholarship. In this workshop sample,) Tj
T*
(many opportunities use one of three patterns:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Minimum 2.5 GPA for access-focused scholarships) Tj
T*
(- Minimum 3.0 GPA for general merit scholarships) Tj
T*
(- Minimum 3.5 GPA for highly competitive awards) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Students with lower GPAs should still apply for need-based and community-based) Tj
T*
(opportunities because many programs look at leadership, persistence, work) Tj
T*
(experience, and service.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(FAQ 2: CAN UNDOCUMENTED STUDENTS APPLY?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Some scholarships do not require U.S. citizenship, but others do. Students) Tj
T*
(should read each eligibility section closely. In this workshop sample:) Tj
T*
() Tj
